.TH "CITADEL" "1" "Jul 2026" "AceTeam" "Citadel CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
citadel-gateway - Start the inference gateway proxy with ACET metering


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBcitadel gateway [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Starts a local HTTP reverse proxy that sits in front of an inference engine
(vLLM, Ollama, etc.) and meters all OpenAI-compatible API requests.

.PP
Metered endpoints:
  /v1/chat/completions   - Chat completions
  /v1/completions        - Text completions
  /v1/embeddings         - Embeddings

.PP
All other paths are proxied through without metering.

.PP
Token usage is extracted from OpenAI-compatible responses (both streaming and
non-streaming) and recorded to ~/.citadel-cli/gateway/transactions.jsonl.

.PP
ACET pricing tiers:
  small   (0-8B params)    1 ACET per 1K tokens  ($0.001)
  medium  (8-70B params)   5 ACET per 1K tokens  ($0.005)
  large   (70-400B params) 25 ACET per 1K tokens ($0.025)
  xlarge  (400B+ params)   100 ACET per 1K tokens ($0.100)

.PP
Revenue split: 80% operator / 20% platform.

.PP
Examples:
  # Proxy to local Ollama
  citadel gateway --upstream http://localhost:11434

.PP
# Proxy to vLLM with custom port and large model tier
  citadel gateway --port 9090 --upstream http://localhost:8000 --model-tier large

.PP
# With ACET settlement enabled
  citadel gateway --upstream http://localhost:11434 --platform https://aceteam.ai/api --api-token act_xxx


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--api-token\fP=""
	API token for ACET settlement (optional)

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for gateway

.PP
\fB--model-tier\fP="medium"
	Pricing tier: small, medium, large, xlarge

.PP
\fB--platform\fP=""
	Platform base URL for ACET settlement (optional)

.PP
\fB--port\fP=8080
	Port to listen on

.PP
\fB--upstream\fP="http://localhost:11434"
	Upstream inference engine URL


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable debug output

.PP
\fB--no-auto-update\fP[=false]
	Disable automatic update checks and installs for this run (or set CITADEL_NO_AUTO_UPDATE=1)

.PP
\fB--no-color\fP[=false]
	Disable colorized output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBcitadel(1)\fP
